╭─ Example Solution ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ The table below shows for each value of $x$ which values of $y$ satisfy the  │
│ condition that $(x,y)$ lies on or inside the circle of radius 5 centered at  │
│ the origin. \begin{tabular}{ccc}                                             │
│ $x$ & Constraints & Number of $y$ values \\                                  │
│ $\pm5$ & $y=0$ & 1 \\                                                        │
│ $\pm4$ & $-3\leq y \leq 3$ & 7 \\                                            │
│ $\pm3$ & $-4\leq y \leq 4$ & 9 \\                                            │
│ $\pm2$ & $-4\leq y\leq 4$ & 9 \\                                             │
│ $\pm1$ & $-4\leq y\leq 4$ & 9 \\                                             │
│ 0 & $-5\leq y\leq 5$ & 11 \\                                                 │
│ \end{tabular} In total, there are $2(1+7+9+9+9)+11=\boxed{81}$ lattice       │
│ points on or inside the circle.                                              │
