   \[
   \text{Volume of the larger hole} = \pi (1.5)^2 \times 8 = \pi \times 2.25 \times 8 = 18\pi \text{ cubic centimeters}
   \]

The total volume of the holes is:
\[
16\pi + 18\pi = 34\pi \text{ cubic centimeters}
\]

Subtracting the total volume of the holes from the volume of the bowling ball gives the fitted volume:
\[
4500\pi - 34\pi = 4466\pi \text{ cubic centimeters}
\]

